```

Then, modify your `ImageGrid` component to include the `Pagination` component. Use the `current` and `pageSize` props to control the page and limit, and the `onChange` prop to update these states when the page changes.

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { Pagination } from 'antd';
import axios from 'axios';

function ImageGrid() {
  // ...
  const [total, setTotal] = useState(0); // Total number of images for pagination

  useEffect(() => {
    // Include total count in the API response or fetch it from a separate endpoint
    async function fetchImages() {
      try {
        const response = await axios.get(`http://localhost:8000/api/dataset/image?page=${page - 1}&limit=${limit}`);
        // Assuming the response includes a total count
        setImages(response.data.images);
        setTotal(response.data.total);
      } catch (error) {
        // Handle errors as before
      }
    }

    fetchImages();
  }, [page, limit]);

  // ...

  return (
    <div>
      {/* The existing code to display images */}

      <Pagination
        current={page}
        pageSize={limit}
        total={total}
        onChange={(page, pageSize) => {
          // Update the page and limit states
          setPage(page);
          setLimit(pageSize);
        }}
        showSizeChanger  // Set this to true to allow changing the limit (page size)
        onShowSizeChange={(current, size) => {
          setLimit(size); // Update the limit when the shown size is changed
        }}
        pageSizeOptions={['10', '20', '50', '100']} // Options for pageSize
      />
      {/* The existing code to display the modal */}
    </div>
  );
}

export default ImageGrid;
```

The `Pagination` component has several props that can be useful:

- `current`: The current page number.
- `pageSize`: The number of items per page.
- `total`: The total number of items.
- `onChange`: A callback function that is called when the page number is changed.
- `showSizeChanger`: A boolean that, when set to `true`, makes a page size changer appear so the user can change the number of items per page.
- `onShowSizeChange`: A callback function that is called when the page size is changed.

Make sure your backend API supports pagination and can handle parameters such as page index and page size (`limit`). Also, ensure that the response from the API includes the total number of images, which is needed to configure the `Pagination` component correctly.

Now, when the user interacts with the `Pagination` controls at the bottom of the `ImageGrid`, the page and limit states in your component will be updated accordingly, triggering a new fetch with the updated parameters.
